All the examples I can find of &#39;.limit&#39; and &#39;.count&#39; properties being 
set use the FileHandler full name, not the class logger name. For example:

java.util.logging.FileHandler.limit=50000
java.util.logging.FileHandler.count=1

Perhaps that&#39;s the issue? (I don&#39;t know if these can be reset on a 
specific FileHandler, as opposed to all FileHandlers.)

